  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Boil</strong> a kettle</p>\r\n<p><strong>Preheat</strong> the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cut</strong> all the potatoes to roughly 4cm chunks, keeping the skins on</p>\r\n<p><strong>Grate</strong> the cheddar for step 6</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the potatoes and salt (optional) to a pot with a lid, cover with boiled water by 5cm and bring to the boil with a lid on a high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> boiling, boil for 5-7 min, or until you can pierce them easily with a knife, then drain and steam dry for 5 min in a colander</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reserve</strong> the pot for step 7</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, slice the leeks in half lengthways, discarding the root ends</p>\r\n<p><strong>Slice</strong> the lengths into 1cm slices, then wash the sliced leek in a colander under the cold tap to remove any grit</p>\r\n<p><strong>Peel</strong> and finely chop or grate the garlic</p>\r\n<p><strong>Heat</strong> a large pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> (2 tsp)</span> of olive oil on a high heat</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>When</strong> hot, add the chicken, leek and garlic with a pinch of salt</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cook</strong> for 4-6 min or until the chicken is lightly golden on the outside (it will continue cooking later) and the leeks have softened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Transfer</strong> the chicken and softened leek to a plate</p>\r\n<p><strong>Return</strong> the pan to a medium-low heat and melt 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">(60g)</span> of butter</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> melted, stir in 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">(60g)</span> of flour and cook for 2-3 min, whisking constantly - this is your 'roux'</p>\r\n<p><strong>Whisk</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">(400ml)</span> of milk gradually&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the bay leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">(ves)</span> and stir constantly until a smooth, thickened sauce remains</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> the sauce has thickened, remove the pan from the heat and stir in the chicken and leek mixture, the cheddar and half of the Dijon mustard&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Season</strong> generously with salt and pepper</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Return</strong> the steamed potatoes to their cooking pot and crush them lightly with a masher (and a knob of butter, optional)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Transfer</strong> the mixture to a baking dish and top with the crushed potatoes, then oven roast for 10 min or until bubbling</p>\r\n<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, combine the remaining Dijon with the vinegar and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(3 tbsp)</span> of olive oil to make a dressing</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/448.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Taste</strong> your dressing and season with salt and pepper</p>\r\n<p><strong>Wash</strong> and finely shred the little gem, discarding the root end<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Toss</strong> the dressing through the salad and serve alongside the chicken pie</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
